## Routing Policy (Advisory)

The system selects a model for each step using this decision order
(first match wins). This policy is informational — the deterministic
`select_model()` function is the source of truth; if prose and code
disagree, code wins.

1. **Budget pressure.** When total spend reaches
   {{ budget_downgrade_pct }}% of the per-task cap, downgrade to the
   fast tier regardless of other signals.
2. **Retryable error.** If the last step failed with a transient
   error (HTTP 429/503), re-run the same model after the configured
   backoff. Do not change models on transient failures.
3. **Escalation.** After {{ escalate_after_failures }} consecutive
   non-retryable failures, escalate to a capable-tier model. Cap
   total escalations at {{ max_escalations }} per task.
4. **Planning first step.** Use a capable-tier model on step 0 to
   draft the plan; subsequent steady-state steps may downgrade.
5. **Steady state.** Otherwise, default to the fast tier.
